programme.title: 177" Giant Buck At 10 Yards On The Ground, A One In A Million Hunting Season
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we take a deep dive into one of the most epic single season stories ever captured in the whitetail woods. A roller coaster filled with the lowest of lows to the highest of highs, we couldn't be more excited to share this one with you. Kaleb Greiner entered the 2023 hunting season with high hopes but he could have never predicted what followed next. Between stacking up a hitlist that included 3 bucks over 175", an EHD outbreak that decimates the deer heard, and a face to face 10 yard bow shot with a 177" giant, this is the story of Kaleb's one in a million hunting season here in Iowa.

programme.title: Giant Rut-Crazed River Farm Buck At 5 Yards, Mike's Best Bow Hunting Strategies
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we sit down with Mike Reed in Iowa as he takes us through the story of yet another River Farm legend he calls "Fitzmagic." With encounters dating back to the early days of hunting the river bottom in 2019, Mike dissects the buck's patterns and the area in which he lived that ultimately led to getting an opportunity at the 7.5 year old brute. Mike dives into multiple stand locations spanning the newer addition to the main River Farm, what he has learned over the past few years of hunting the area and many more lessons learned along the way. We hope you enjoy and be sure to tune in over the coming weeks as we continue to bring more awesome hunt action your way! Thank you as always for the support.

programme.title: Two Perfect Hunts With The Reed Family, Reading The Christmas Story
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we bring you a show that has a little bit of everything. Kicking things off, we join Chad Holmes who reads us the Christmas Story and discusses the true meaning of Christmas. Following that we join Mike and Bella Reed who bring us up to speed on what has been happening in the woods since Mike tagged out on "Fitzmagic" back in November. Finally, we join the Reed family during the shotgun seasons as two perfect hunts unfold on the same bean field. Up first is Kathryn Reed who makes it to the woods for her first hunt of the year. With the wrong wind direction to hunt the current Redneck Blind setup, Mike gets mobile and moves a trailer blind into place. The move pays off BIG and Kathryn has the perfect hunt and builds another memory. Then, we jump to the same field only a few days later with Brynn Reed who's hoping to pull off the same feat as her mom! Little did she know the biggest buck of her life would walk into the field and after following her shooting process, a perfectly placed bullet closes the chapter on a true surprise buck. As always, thank you from all of us at Midwest Whitetail for taking the time to watch and for supporting us this entire season. Merry Christmas to each and every one of you and good luck the next time you hit the woods!

programme.title: Redemption On A Public Land Stud, Gavin's Bowhunting Journey
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we tag along with Midwest Whitetail editor Gavin Koterba as he takes us through a multi year quest that ends with him tagging his biggest buck to date. After making the move to Iowa to chase his dream, Gavin's goal has been to shoot a buck on public land. With years of scouting under his belt, multiple encounters with giant bucks, and an attitude to learn as much as possible along the way, hopes were extremely high going into the 2023 deer season. Follow along on the roller coaster ride that ultimately ends in Gavin tagging his biggest buck ever. As always, we can't say thank you enough for the continued support and hope you have a great rest of the deer season!

programme.title: Hunting Intern Chases A Dream, Jenna Makes A Perfect Shot On A Giant 8
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we kick things off joining Drake Lamb, Justin Karns and sister Jenna in southern Iowa. With a great food source to hunt, the trio key in on a big 8 that has been frequenting the area with hopes of trying to fill Jenna's first buck tag of the season. After hunting her tail off all fall, she finally gets her opportunity and makes a perfect shot. Next, Josh Sparks joins us with an important announcement about the opening or the Midwest Whitetail internship opportunity for the upcoming 2024 season. If you are interested in applying, be sure to visit our social media pages for more information that will be released soon! Finally, on the topic of interns, we shift our focus to catching up with Shea McTighe who was a part of the 2023 internship class here at Midwest Whitetail. Shea talks through why he was interested in the internship, what he learned throughout his time here, and generally speaking talks through his take aways while here. After putting in a ton of work throughout the season following Kaleb Greiner with a camera and maintaining editing tasks, Shea's hunting opportunity arose during the 2nd shotgun season in Iowa and as you'll see, he made the most of it. Refelcting on the past year we could not be more grateful for the week to week support from all of the viewers, and want to wish each of you a very Happy New Year. We can't wait to see what 2024 will bring!

programme.title: Handmade 2: A Journey Through Perfect Waves and Handshaped Boards
programme.desc: On paper, shaping yourself a surfboard by hand would seem like a giant pain in the ass. Shaping bays are small, dusty, sweat-inducing spaces. Planer whirs are not anyone's preferred soundtrack. You'll make a lot of shit surfboards on your way to the first one that rides at all like you want it to. But when you stick it out, the journey changes you and it changes your surfing in some wonderful ways, and you realize that the thing that seemed like such a pain has become something incomparably fun. Case in point: Alex Knost, Ellis Ericson, Andrew Doheny and Shyama Buttonshaw. These four surfers, the stars of the film above, started their handshaping journeys many years ago. And amid all the clouds of foam dust they learned a thing or two about how their equipment works and what feelings they wanted to chase in their surfing. It's had some profound effects on their style of riding waves, but more importantly, they'll be the first to tell you that it's been a ridiculous amount of fun. Press play above to get some insights into the unique surfing and surfcraft of these DIYers as they test out self-shapes in pulsing Indonesian surf.

For the past 10 years, Weiland has scoured obscure coastlines at extreme latitudes searching for waves in some of the coldest, most inhospitable places imaginable. In the process, he's uncovered new waves and redefined surf exploration. Coldwater Journal documents Weiland's journey with fellow fringe wave connoisseurs Alex Gray, Dane Gudauskas, Timmy Reyes, Sam Hammer, Cyrus Sutton, Keith Malloy and more as they chase swells to the furthest-flung destinations and face the kinds of challenges most surfers could never conceive.
